title: 'cuModuleGetFunction(&function, module, kernel_name)' failed with 'CUDA_ERROR_INVALID_HANDLE'
body:
### Is there an existing issue for this?

- [X] I have searched the existing issues

### Bug description

I encountered the titled error when starting the training from the GUI. I don't have a clue how to solve the problem. I confirmed that GPU is recognized by tensorflow-gpu. CUDA version is 11.2, and cuDNN version 8.2, tensorflow-gpu version is 2.6.0. 

### Operating System

Windows 10

### DeepLabCut version

deeplabcut 2.2.1.1

### DeepLabCut mode

single animal

### Device type

gpu

### Steps To Reproduce

_No response_
